Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.52,0:00:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.14,0:00:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Focus Interaction in
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.04,0:00:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,tvOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.83,0:00:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Matt, I'm a software
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.09,0:00:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,engineer working on UIKit and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.74,0:00:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be joined later today by my
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.15,0:00:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,colleague Jon.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.98,0:00:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a lot to cover today, so
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.24,0:00:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,let's get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.94,0:00:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we're going to showcase
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.13,0:00:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,some of the new features and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.33,0:00:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,enhancements that we've made for
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.03,0:00:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus Interaction support in
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.64,0:00:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,tvOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.67,0:00:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,These cover a number of requests
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.06,0:00:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that we've received from you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.16,0:00:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,over the past year.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.89,0:00:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, Focus Interaction support
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.50,0:00:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,is now in SceneKit and so we're
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.62,0:00:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,going to cover everything that
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.67,0:01:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you need to know in order to get
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.23,0:01:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,started.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.06,0:01:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, we've built some
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.68,0:01:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,great new focus debugging tools
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.97,0:01:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in tvOS 11 for helping you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.56,0:01:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,diagnose focus related issues in
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.97,0:01:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.32,0:01:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We think these new tools are
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.27,0:01:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,going to save you a ton of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.57,0:01:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But before we start it's
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.98,0:01:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,important that we review some of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.42,0:01:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the basics of how the Focus API
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.10,0:01:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,works into tvOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.16,0:01:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This information is going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.38,0:01:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,important throughout our session
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.68,0:01:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.28,0:01:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,From the perspective of the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.36,0:01:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,focus engine your app is app is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.93,0:01:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,made up of focus items and focus
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.54,0:01:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,environments.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.72,0:01:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus items are the user
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.65,0:01:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,interface elements that are
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.10,0:01:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,capable of becoming focused.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.39,0:01:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They conform to the UIFocusItem
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.19,0:01:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,item protocol.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.46,0:01:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Examples of focus items include
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.50,0:01:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,UIViews in UIKit and nodes in
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.42,0:01:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,SpriteKit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.17,0:01:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus environments conform to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.11,0:01:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the UIFocusEnvironment protocol.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.21,0:01:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Environments are allowed to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.48,0:01:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,influence the focus behavior in
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.20,0:02:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,your application and they also
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.86,0:02:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,get notified about focus
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.10,0:02:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,updates.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.50,0:02:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All focus items are also focus
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.50,0:02:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,environments, but these also
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.45,0:02:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,cover other objects like view
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.87,0:02:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,controllers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.10,0:02:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus items and focus
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.54,0:02:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,environments are arranged in a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.03,0:02:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,hierarchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.20,0:02:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,In UIKit this hierarchy loosely
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.84,0:02:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,follows the view and view
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.28,0:02:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,controller hierarchies and in
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.85,0:02:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,SpriteKit it follows the node
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.38,0:02:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,hierarchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.60,0:02:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This hierarchy is important when
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.43,0:02:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it comes to getting notified
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.61,0:02:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,about focus updates.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.25,0:02:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,A focus update can happen in one
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.21,0:02:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of two ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.60,0:02:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,First, a user can move focus
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.90,0:02:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,geometrically, such as by
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.18,0:02:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,swiping on the Siri remote or
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.47,0:02:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,your app can trigger a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.57,0:02:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,programmatic focus update, such
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.18,0:02:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,as by calling APIs like
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.79,0:02:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,setNeedsFocusUpdate.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.47,0:02:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When a focus update happens, we
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.38,0:02:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,notify every focus environment
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.34,0:02:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that contains both the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.02,0:02:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,previously focused item and the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.02,0:02:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,next focused item.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.37,0:02:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And this includes all common
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.82,0:02:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,ancestor environments as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.86,0:03:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We notify environments in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.18,0:03:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,ascending order starting with
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.52,0:03:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the two items that are directly
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.16,0:03:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,involved in the update.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.35,0:03:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Notifications are sent by
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.57,0:03:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,calling the didUpdateFocus
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.17,0:03:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,method, which is defined on the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.71,0:03:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,UIFocusEnvironment protocol.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.86,0:03:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And this leads us straight into
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.27,0:03:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,our first topic of today, which
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.11,0:03:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is that in tvOS 11 we're
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.16,0:03:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,providing a few helpful new ways
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.46,0:03:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to get notified about focus
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.88,0:03:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,updates.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.89,0:03:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's jump back to that diagram.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.07,0:03:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I was just saying, we
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.07,0:03:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,notify your app using this
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.74,0:03:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,didUpdateFocus method defined on
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.78,0:03:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,UIFocusEnvironment.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.39,0:03:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But sometimes there might be
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.61,0:03:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,another object in your app not a
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.42,0:03:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,focus environment that you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.02,0:03:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,want to be loosely coupled to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.24,0:03:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the rest of your user interface
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.46,0:03:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,code.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.56,0:03:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for this case we're
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.23,0:03:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,introducing a new foundation
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.85,0:03:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,notification type called
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.31,0:03:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,UIFocusDidUpdate.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.48,0:03:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can observe this from
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.65,0:03:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere in your app and it will
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.89,0:03:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,get sent every time focus
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.43,0:03:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,updates.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.69,0:03:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This notification includes all
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.17,0:03:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the same information that you're
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.43,0:04:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,used to getting for a normal
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.46,0:04:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,focus update, including a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.27,0:04:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,context that describes the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.04,0:04:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,update, as well as an animation
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.17,0:04:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,coordinator for controlling
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.50,0:04:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,visual feedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.04,0:04:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You can access both of these
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.60,0:04:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,objects using two new user info
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.91,0:04:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,keys that we're providing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.60,0:04:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The UIFocusUpdateContext key and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.76,0:04:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the UIFocusUpdate
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.15,0:04:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,AnimiationCoordinator key.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.16,0:04:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We're also introducing another
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.86,0:04:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,key notification type related to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.55,0:04:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,focus updates and that's called
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.69,0:04:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,UIFocusMovementDidFail and this
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.69,0:04:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,notification is sent whenever
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.09,0:04:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the user tries, but fails to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.63,0:04:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,move focus in a certain
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.83,0:04:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.92,0:04:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This will only be sent when the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.68,0:04:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,user is trying to move focus not
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.79,0:04:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,when your app fails to perform
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.81,0:04:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,some kind of programmatic focus
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.04,0:04:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,update.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.89,0:04:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is really useful for
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.09,0:04:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,cases where you might want to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.34,0:04:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,provide some kind of feedback to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.71,0:04:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the user when they try to move
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.31,0:04:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,focus in a direction that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.30,0:04:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,they're not allowed to.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.55,0:04:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Now a good example of this is on
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.09,0:04:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple TV where VoiceOver will
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.08,0:05:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,provide a sound when a user
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.14,0:05:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,tries to move focus in a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.49,0:05:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,direction that they're not
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.18,0:05:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,allowed to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.85,0:05:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is a really helpful way
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.37,0:05:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to provide some extra auditory
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.14,0:05:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,feedback to visually impaired
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.93,0:05:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,users letting them know that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.74,0:05:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,their action was appropriately
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.07,0:05:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,received, but that it didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.65,0:05:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,have any effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.89,0:05:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's it for focus update
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.98,0:05:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,notifications.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.69,0:05:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We're also providing a few new
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.83,0:05:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,helpful protocol extensions on
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.50,0:05:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the UIFocusEnvironment and
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.09,0:05:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,UIFocusItem protocols to help
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.35,0:05:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you write more succinct and
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.70,0:05:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,safer code.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.83,0:05:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The first of these is a pretty
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.99,0:05:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,easy one we're adding an
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.26,0:05:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,isFocused property to the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.43,0:05:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,UIFocusItem protocol and this is
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.38,0:05:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,just a simple way to check if
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.28,0:05:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,any item is currently focused.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.51,0:05:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We've exposed this property on
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.87,0:05:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,UIView since tvOS 9, but now
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.37,0:05:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're exposing it on the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.83,0:05:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,protocol UIFocusItem item
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.38,0:05:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,directly you can use this with
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.13,0:05:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,any type of focus item and that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.42,0:05:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,includes SpriteKit nodes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.32,0:06:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We've also added a new contains
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.58,0:06:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,method to the UIFocusEnvironment
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.51,0:06:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,protocol.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.85,0:06:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This method allows you to easily
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.15,0:06:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,check if one focus environment
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.25,0:06:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,contains another focus
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.52,0:06:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,environment, but without having
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.36,0:06:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to know the underlying types
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.53,0:06:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,involved in the check.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.15,0:06:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's look at an example of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.03,0:06:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.33,0:06:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Suppose we want to check if an
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.00,0:06:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,item that just got focused is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.33,0:06:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,contained by our current view
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.91,0:06:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.43,0:06:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We can accomplish this by simply
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.38,0:06:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,calling the contains method on
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.78,0:06:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the view controller itself and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.56,0:06:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,passing in the next focus item
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.91,0:06:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.31,0:06:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This will work if that item is a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.84,0:06:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,view, it'll work if it's a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.96,0:06:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,SpriteKit node, it doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.21,0:06:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,matter what the types are
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.07,0:06:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,involved, you can just call
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.66,0:06:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,contains and it'll just work.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.50,0:06:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, this will hopefully cut
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.89,0:06:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,down on the amount of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.80,0:06:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,typecasting that you have to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.76,0:06:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,perform in your code.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.73,0:06:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's it for new protocol
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.99,0:06:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,extensions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.96,0:06:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,For our next enhancements, I'd
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.95,0:06:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,like to invite up my colleague
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.29,0:06:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Jon to talk to you about some
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.15,0:06:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,new APIs for focus animations.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.15,0:07:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Good morning, last year we
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.09,0:07:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,showed you the coordination API
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.89,0:07:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can use to keep your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.62,0:07:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,animations in sync with the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.15,0:07:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,system animations during a focus
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.94,0:07:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,update.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.21,0:07:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is done by using the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.58,0:07:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,UIFocusAnimationCoordinator that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.13,0:07:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is provided whenever a focus
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.15,0:07:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,update occurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.62,0:07:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, I'd like to talk to you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.89,0:07:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,about some enhancements that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.77,0:07:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,we've made to this API in tvOS
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.37,0:07:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,11.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.62,0:07:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But before I get started let's
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.71,0:07:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,take a more in-depth look at how
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.32,0:07:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,animations work today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.22,0:07:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus animations are a really
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.18,0:07:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,important part of the tvOS user
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.89,0:07:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.05,0:07:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only do they show your users
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.54,0:07:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,where focus has moved they help
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.36,0:07:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,them feel more connected with
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.69,0:07:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,your content.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.74,0:07:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But as with most things, timing
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.21,0:07:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is essential.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.96,0:07:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If the animations are too fast
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.54,0:07:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,it creates a jarring effect for
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.93,0:07:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,your users.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.89,0:07:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And if they're too slow well
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.46,0:07:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,they're getting in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.25,0:07:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So, UIKit has a lot of work put
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.99,0:07:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,into it to manage these
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.33,0:07:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,animations and their timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.12,0:07:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We do a lot of manipulations,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.93,0:08:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,such as duration changes, to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.52,0:08:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,keep the animations feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.79,0:08:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,fluid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.13,0:08:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Quicker movements through
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.58,0:08:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple focus items will result
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.16,0:08:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in quicker animations.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.67,0:08:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we move slowly from one
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.20,0:08:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,item to the next we slow down
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.06,0:08:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the animations to match.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.36,0:08:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,When a user moves focus to an
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.97,0:08:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,item offscreen we make sure to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.16,0:08:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,add an appropriate delay until
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.36,0:08:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that item is fully visible
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.64,0:08:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,before we perform the focusing
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.02,0:08:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,animations.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.64,0:08:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And you might have noticed that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.12,0:08:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,focusing animations and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.64,0:08:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,unfocusing animations have a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.43,0:08:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,different set of timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.38,0:08:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This is because focusing
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.76,0:08:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,animations should be prominent
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.01,0:08:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and they should grab the user's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.21,0:08:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,attention, whereas unfocusing
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.11,0:08:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,animations should be subtler and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.76,0:08:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,more in the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.64,0:08:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can see here as focus
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.62,0:08:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,moves between these items, the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.75,0:08:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,item becoming focused pops up
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.21,0:08:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,very quickly and the item
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.44,0:08:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,becoming unfocused slowly moves
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.64,0:08:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,into the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.28,0:08:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it leaves a trail
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.33,0:09:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,behind it as focus has moved
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.29,0:09:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,from it to the next item.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.30,0:09:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when you call
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.06,0:09:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,addCoordinatedAnimations to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.51,0:09:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,synchronize your animations we
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.71,0:09:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically determine whether
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.72,0:09:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,these are focusing or unfocusing
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.38,0:09:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,animations based on the focus
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.98,0:09:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,environment hierarchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.22,0:09:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here's the same diagram Matt
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.81,0:09:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,showed earlier for the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.84,0:09:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,didUpdateFocus notifications.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.56,0:09:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever you call
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.54,0:09:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,addCoordinatedAnimations from
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.24,0:09:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,either the previously focused
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.62,0:09:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,item or any of its direct
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.35,0:09:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,ancestors up to but not
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.62,0:09:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,including the common parent
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.98,0:09:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,environment we consider these
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.28,0:09:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,unfocusing animations and we
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.02,0:09:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,coordinate them as such.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.68,0:09:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Conversely, if your animations
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.23,0:09:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,are added from either the next
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.36,0:09:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,focused item or any of its
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.26,0:09:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,direct ancestors we consider
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.96,0:09:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,these focusing animations and so
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.70,0:09:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,they get that more prominent
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.96,0:09:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.91,0:09:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And this works really well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.74,0:09:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But in tvOS 11 we're now
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.54,0:10:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,allowing you to specifically
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.83,0:10:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,target either the focusing or
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.19,0:10:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,unfocusing animations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.05,0:10:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're doing this by adding
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.76,0:10:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,two new methods to the UIFocus
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.35,0:10:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,AnimationCoordinator,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.96,0:10:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,addCoordinated
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.83,0:10:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,FocusingAnimations and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.45,0:10:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,addCoordinated
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.24,0:10:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,UnfocusingAnimations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.72,0:10:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, addCoordinated
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.18,0:10:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,FocusingAnimations will function
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.84,0:10:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly the same as if you call
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.97,0:10:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,addCoordinatedAnimations from
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.92,0:10:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,within the next focused item or
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.86,0:10:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,any of its direct ancestors.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.89,0:10:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And addCoordinated
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.83,0:10:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,UnfocusingAnimations will
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.94,0:10:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,function the same as
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.80,0:10:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,addCoordinatedAnimations from
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.52,0:10:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,within the previous focused item
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.33,0:10:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,or its ancestors.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.60,0:10:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, the best way to show you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.91,0:10:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,how this works is with a demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.62,0:10:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's dive right in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.06,0:10:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so I'm working a very
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.83,0:10:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,simple timeline application that
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.42,0:10:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,shows some entries from past
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.95,0:10:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,dubdub events and their
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.04,0:10:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,keynotes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.51,0:10:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And each entry is represented by
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.42,0:10:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,this cell that has a number in
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.98,0:11:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it and as we move focus the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.13,0:11:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,corresponding image above moves
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.14,0:11:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,down to give a little bit of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.24,0:11:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,emphasis.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.14,0:11:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,As I move through these you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.02,0:11:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,might notice that it feels a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.42,0:11:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,little bit choppy as we move
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.15,0:11:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.93,0:11:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well let's hop over and take a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.73,0:11:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,look at the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.51,0:11:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll see that everything
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.95,0:11:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is done within the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.39,0:11:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,addCoordinatedAnimations block.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.65,0:11:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is a great use for our
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.29,0:11:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,new API, what we have here is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.25,0:11:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the focusing view and I've
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.50,0:11:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,gotten a reference to this by
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.03,0:11:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,using the nextFocusedIndexPath
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.61,0:11:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to grab the supplementary view
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.89,0:11:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it corresponds with and I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.34,0:11:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,simply doing a transform of 100
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.27,0:11:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,points down.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.96,0:11:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And then similarly for the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.46,0:11:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,unfocusing view the image that's
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.17,0:11:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,going back up I get it by using
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.25,0:11:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the previouslyFocusedIndexPath
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.15,0:11:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and then transforming to the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.43,0:11:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.44,0:12:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of using the single
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.08,0:12:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,addCoordinatedAnimations call
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.04,0:12:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which in fact makes everything
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.68,0:12:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,coordinate alongside the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.68,0:12:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,focusing animations, we can now
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.47,0:12:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,split this up into two explicit
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.16,0:12:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,calls, one for the focusing
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.07,0:12:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,animations for the focusing view
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.26,0:12:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and then one for the unfocusing
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.24,0:12:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,animations for the unfocusing
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.70,0:12:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,view.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.29,0:12:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, now let's rerun this and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.88,0:12:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.10,0:12:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now as we move from one item to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.32,0:12:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the next you can see that the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.11,0:12:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,same trail as focus moves in the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.35,0:12:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,cells itself exists in the image
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.94,0:12:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,views themselves and this
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.98,0:12:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,creates a much nicer user
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.55,0:12:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,experience for your application.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.48,0:12:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so now let's hope
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.81,0:12:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,back over to the slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.50,0:12:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's one other thing I'd
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.63,0:12:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,like to talk about regarding
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.00,0:12:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,animations.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.56,0:12:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition to the two new
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.52,0:13:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,methods we're also providing an
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.14,0:13:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,instance of the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.02,0:13:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,UIFocusAnimationContext and this
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.32,0:13:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is a new object in tvOS 11 that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.37,0:13:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,gives you some additional timing
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.04,0:13:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,information about the animations
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.63,0:13:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,occurring which should make
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.09,0:13:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,advance animations even easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.10,0:13:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's say we'd like to run
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.81,0:13:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,an animation during the second
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.22,0:13:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,half of the system focusing
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.96,0:13:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,animations.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.62,0:13:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well this is very easy to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.33,0:13:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,all we need to do is grab the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.41,0:13:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,duration off of the animation
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.55,0:13:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,context, divide it by two, and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.97,0:13:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,then pass these values into the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.73,0:13:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,standard UIView animate method
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.92,0:13:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're done.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.34,0:13:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,One important point to mention
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.02,0:13:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is the overrideInheritedDuration
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.90,0:13:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,option that needs to get passed
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.13,0:13:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in because without this the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.88,0:13:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,nested view based animations are
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.77,0:13:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,going to ignore the duration
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.29,0:13:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that you gave and instead use
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.64,0:13:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the outer duration.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.53,0:13:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But this doesn't just make you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.43,0:13:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,UIVIewAnimation easier it also
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.41,0:13:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,provides better non-UIKit
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.22,0:13:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,support.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.93,0:13:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you're using SpriteKit
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.26,0:13:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,which is fully supported by the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.45,0:13:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,focus system it allows you to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.37,0:14:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,create a more consistent feel
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.48,0:14:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,for your animations using SK
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.17,0:14:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,actions for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.49,0:14:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an example of using SK
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.42,0:14:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,actions to fade the opacity to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.24,0:14:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,50% using the exact same timing
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.35,0:14:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that the system UIKit focusing
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.40,0:14:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,animations would.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.70,0:14:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the existing API
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.14,0:14:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,works really well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.26,0:14:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you don't have a need to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.93,0:14:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,explicitly target either
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.25,0:14:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,focusing or unfocusing continue
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.19,0:14:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,using the existing API because
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.02,0:14:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it does the right thing for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.21,0:14:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if you need to target
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.16,0:14:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,your animations to focusing or
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.79,0:14:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,unfocusing regardless of their
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.87,0:14:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,association with the focus
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.29,0:14:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,environment hierarchy use the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.15,0:14:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,new APIs and you'll be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.45,0:14:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,do that to great effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.10,0:14:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And lastly, the focus animation
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.70,0:14:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,context is provided for some
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.18,0:14:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,additional timing information
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.82,0:14:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,which should make advanced
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.59,0:14:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,animations even easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.18,0:14:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, next I'd like to talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.01,0:14:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,focus sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.09,0:14:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Where animations give a visual
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.48,0:14:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,representation of the focus
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.81,0:15:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,update focus sounds provide an
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.02,0:15:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,auditory queue to the user that
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.80,0:15:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,focus has moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.20,0:15:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And just like animations there's
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.40,0:15:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,some subtlety to sound playback
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.50,0:15:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to create the best user
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.52,0:15:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,experience possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.06,0:15:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,UIKit performs a number of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.61,0:15:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,volume and panning modifications
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.14,0:15:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to every sound that's played.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.43,0:15:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, faster focus movements
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.27,0:15:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,result in a quieter sound and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.94,0:15:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,slower focus movements result in
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.71,0:15:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,a louder sound, which nicely
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.96,0:15:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,complements the same duration
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.26,0:15:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,modifications we make to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.44,0:15:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,animations.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.15,0:15:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We also use the location of the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.88,0:15:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,focusing item onscreen to pan
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.61,0:15:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the volume either stereo left or
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.18,0:15:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,stereo right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.28,0:15:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you swipe right across
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.83,0:15:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the screen you'll notice sound
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.04,0:15:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,starts to pan to the right and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.45,0:15:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,as you swipe back left you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.34,0:15:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,notice sound pans to the left
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.04,0:15:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,bouncing out when focus is
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.36,0:15:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,centered horizontally.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.54,0:15:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, this helps create a much
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.00,0:15:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,more immersive user experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.31,0:16:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But a lot of requested that we
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.40,0:16:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,allow you to provide custom
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.82,0:16:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,focus sounds or to opt out of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.29,0:16:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the UIKit sounds and started in
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.32,0:16:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,tvOS 11 I'm happy to announce
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.17,0:16:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're allowing you to do
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.10,0:16:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,both.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.57,0:16:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to play custom sounds you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.08,0:16:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,simply need to register your
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.75,0:16:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,sound with an identifier and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.72,0:16:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,then provide that identifier
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.72,0:16:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,during a focus update that will
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.33,0:16:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,play a focus sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.57,0:16:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This is only a user initiated
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.36,0:16:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,focus movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.64,0:16:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And then once we have that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.71,0:16:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,identifier we'll play the sound
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.61,0:16:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,it's associated with.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.56,0:16:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,To register sounds you'll use a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.13,0:16:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,class method register
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.61,0:16:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,soundFileURL for sound
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.26,0:16:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,identifier which is exposed on
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.11,0:16:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the new UIFocusSystem, a new
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.03,0:16:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,object in tvOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.02,0:16:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The sound registration is a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.12,0:16:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,global action, meaning that once
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.02,0:16:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you do it that custom sound is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.72,0:16:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,available throughout your entire
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.06,0:16:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,application.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.07,0:17:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of this, you should only
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.93,0:17:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,register a sound for a single
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.81,0:17:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,identifier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.06,0:17:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, reregistering with the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.65,0:17:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,same sound identifier is an
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.09,0:17:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,error.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.67,0:17:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's perfectly acceptable
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.08,0:17:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and reasonable to have multiple
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.70,0:17:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds in your application, just
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.22,0:17:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,give each one of them a unique
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.69,0:17:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,identifier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.68,0:17:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's global you also
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.32,0:17:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,want to register early.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.62,0:17:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a nontrivial performance
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.22,0:17:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,cost to setting up your custom
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.62,0:17:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds for playback and we want
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.39,0:17:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to make sure there's as much
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.33,0:17:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,time between registration and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.22,0:17:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,user focus movement so that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.76,0:17:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds can play seamlessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.10,0:17:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The registration method accepts
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.94,0:17:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,all standard iOS file formats
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.37,0:17:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that are locally stored on your
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.64,0:17:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,device.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.73,0:17:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when you actually need to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.55,0:17:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,play the sound you'll use the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.82,0:17:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,new optional method on the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.15,0:17:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,UIFocusEnvironment protocol.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.00,0:17:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we call this method
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.62,0:17:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,soundIdentifier
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.38,0:17:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,ForFocusUpdate.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.78,0:17:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In the same ascending order that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.88,0:17:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the didUpdateFocus notifications
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.68,0:18:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,are delivered.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.25,0:18:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And we start by calling this
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.62,0:18:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,method on the next focused item.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.14,0:18:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If the next focused item gives
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.02,0:18:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,us a no focus sound identifier
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.28,0:18:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,we use that to control sound
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.69,0:18:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,playback for this focus update
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.13,0:18:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we're done.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.84,0:18:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if we don't get a sound
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.37,0:18:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,identifier back from the next
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.70,0:18:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,focus item we look to its parent
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.46,0:18:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and we try again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.65,0:18:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if the parent doesn't return
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.05,0:18:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,anything we repeat this process
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.59,0:18:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and we go up to its parent and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.08,0:18:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,we repeat this over and over
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.38,0:18:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,until we get to the root focus
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.81,0:18:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,environment which if none of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.83,0:18:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,your focus environments have
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.18,0:18:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,chosen to provide a custom sound
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.97,0:18:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,then we simply use the default
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.23,0:18:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that UIKit would use on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.42,0:18:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there are a number of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.12,0:18:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,options for what values you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.55,0:18:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,might return from sound
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.95,0:18:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,identifier for focus update.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.89,0:18:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, you're able to return
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.25,0:18:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,any of the sounds that you had
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.48,0:18:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,previously registered and doing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.33,0:18:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so will play the sound that that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.00,0:18:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,identifier was registered with.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.52,0:18:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,UIKit also provides two sound
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.10,0:18:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,identifiers, default and none.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.15,0:19:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,By providing the default sound
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.45,0:19:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,identifier it explicitly signals
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.43,0:19:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to UIKit that you want to force
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.01,0:19:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the default sound that UIKit
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.77,0:19:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,would play on its own to be
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.25,0:19:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,played for this focus update.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.99,0:19:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now keep in mind if none of your
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.01,0:19:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,environments wish to control
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.55,0:19:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,sound for this update then this
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.61,0:19:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is value we'll use anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.37,0:19:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's probably rare you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.80,0:19:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,need to use, this provide this
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.22,0:19:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,for the cases that you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.87,0:19:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And last, the non-identifier can
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.66,0:19:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,be used to entirely opt out of
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.44,0:19:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,focus sounds for this focus
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.14,0:19:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,update.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.26,0:19:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You're able to very easily
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.72,0:19:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,conditionally modify which sound
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.10,0:19:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,is played and using the same
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.99,0:19:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,contains protocol extension that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.69,0:19:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Matt showed earlier we're able
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.76,0:19:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to determine when focus moves
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.01,0:19:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,through a particular environment
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.40,0:19:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and when it does modify the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.05,0:19:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,sound, otherwise deferred to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.84,0:19:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,pair it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.12,0:19:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I here I have a particular
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.91,0:19:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,environment, I'll call it sound
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.96,0:19:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,enabled environment where when
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.54,0:19:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,focus moves through this
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.83,0:19:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,environment I want to play a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.24,0:20:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,sound that I registered with my
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.47,0:20:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,custom sound identifier.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.63,0:20:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, it's very easy to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.86,0:20:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,take the next focused item and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.34,0:20:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,then just check whether or not
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.60,0:20:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that's contained within the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.87,0:20:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,sound enabled environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.01,0:20:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, a couple quick points on
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.97,0:20:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,opting out of focus sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.76,0:20:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,First, users expect a sound to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.98,0:20:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,be played when focus movement
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.87,0:20:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,occurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.63,0:20:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I mentioned before, this is
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.84,0:20:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,an auditory queue to them that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.14,0:20:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,focus has moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.88,0:20:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you should only be opting
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.50,0:20:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,out of sounds if the user is
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.67,0:20:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,explicitly expected to.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.23,0:20:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A great example of this might be
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.65,0:20:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,an in-game menu where the user
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.09,0:20:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,can turn off sounds for your
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.82,0:20:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,entire application.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.64,0:20:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, if you were think about
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.49,0:20:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,opting out of focus sounds and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.20,0:20:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,then playing your own when a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.16,0:20:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,focus update occurs, I highly
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.28,0:20:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,encourage you to use our API
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.64,0:20:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,instead because not only do you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.97,0:20:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,get the same volume and panning
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.96,0:20:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,adjustments that we perform for
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.84,0:20:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,our internal sounds which are
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.88,0:20:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,probably very hard to replicate.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.80,0:21:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We also respect the user's
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.21,0:21:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,device settings for playing
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.80,0:21:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,these sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.00,0:21:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Apple TV has a setting that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.40,0:21:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,allows you to turn off
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.21,0:21:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation sounds for the entire
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.00,0:21:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,system and you don't want your
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.46,0:21:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,application to be the only one
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.09,0:21:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,playing sounds if the user says
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.64,0:21:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't want them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.44,0:21:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so to recap.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.39,0:21:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You should use good judgment
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.83,0:21:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,when determining when and where
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.54,0:21:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and which sounds to play for
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.39,0:21:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,focus update because your sound
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.16,0:21:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,should enhance the user
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.25,0:21:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,experience they should not
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.78,0:21:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,detract from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.68,0:21:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,A great example of this might be
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.45,0:21:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,differentiating between elements
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.93,0:21:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,onscreen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.79,0:21:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We do this in UIKit based on the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.72,0:21:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,size of particular items.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.66,0:21:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So, very large focus items have
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.19,0:21:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,a larger, deeper sound and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.41,0:21:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,smaller items have a smaller,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.10,0:21:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,higher pitched sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.05,0:21:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, this is all to enhance
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.68,0:21:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the user experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.42,0:21:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All right and with that I'd like
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.90,0:21:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to turn things back over to Matt
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.76,0:22:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,who will talk about support for
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.01,0:22:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,SceneKit.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.57,0:22:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Matt.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.52,0:22:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.11,0:22:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thanks Jon.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.90,0:22:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, I'm excited to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.45,0:22:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,announce that in tvOS 11 we're
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.53,0:22:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,now extending focus system
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.00,0:22:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,support into the SceneKit
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.85,0:22:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,framework.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.47,0:22:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how does this work?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.95,0:22:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well if you recall back to tvOS
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.61,0:22:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,9 it used to be that UIView was
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.93,0:22:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the only type that was able to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.58,0:22:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,be focused.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.03,0:22:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In tvOS 10 we introduced this
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.89,0:22:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,new UI focused item protocol and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.46,0:22:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,we extended focus interaction
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.15,0:22:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,support into SpriteKit by
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.99,0:22:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,adopting this protocol on both
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.30,0:22:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,UIView and SKNode.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.13,0:22:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Well now in tvOS 11 we're adding
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.56,0:22:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,SCNNode to the UIFocusItem
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.45,0:22:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,family.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.45,0:22:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how does this work?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.68,0:22:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like SpriteKit you need to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.27,0:22:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,opt in in order to get focus
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.26,0:22:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,support in your SceneKit apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.47,0:22:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This means that nodes are not
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.91,0:22:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,focusable by default.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.78,0:23:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to make them focusable
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.52,0:23:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it couldn't be easier, all you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.02,0:23:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,have to do is set the new focus
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.68,0:23:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,behavior property to focusable
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.70,0:23:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's it, it's that easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.80,0:23:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,FocusBehavior is a new property
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.19,0:23:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,on SCNNode and we've also made
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.11,0:23:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,this property available on
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.53,0:23:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,SKNode so now it's even easier
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.21,0:23:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to make your SpriteKit nodes
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.55,0:23:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,focusable as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.24,0:23:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But I think it would be a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.06,0:23:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,more fun to just show you this
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.40,0:23:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in action with a quick demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.07,0:23:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, I've been building a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.83,0:23:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,tic-tac-toe app for tvOS and I
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.75,0:23:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,really wanted my app to just
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.67,0:23:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,have an extra bit of pop and so
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.96,0:23:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided to implement it with
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.32,0:23:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,SceneKit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.32,0:23:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, you can see my
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.38,0:23:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,three-dimensional tic-tac-toe
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.77,0:23:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,board with full perspective and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.36,0:23:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already implement focus
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.62,0:23:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,interaction support in my
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.73,0:23:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,tic-tac-toe game.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.06,0:23:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I can move focus around
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.77,0:23:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,using any type of input device
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.87,0:23:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to each of the tiles on my
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.97,0:23:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,board.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.90,0:23:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I press Select I can drop
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.18,0:23:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,an X or an O anywhere on the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.99,0:23:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,tile, on any tile.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.91,0:24:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, implementing this couldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.00,0:24:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,have been easier, in addition to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.17,0:24:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,just setting up my SceneKit
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.63,0:24:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,scene all I had to do was mark
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.13,0:24:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,each of the nodes that represent
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.27,0:24:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the tiles on the board as
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.70,0:24:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,focusable using that one line
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.30,0:24:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,code I showed earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.22,0:24:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And then provide custom
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.64,0:24:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,animations using those same
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.38,0:24:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,animation APIs that Jon was just
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.43,0:24:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,talking about a moment ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.45,0:24:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's really all that we
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.72,0:24:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,had to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.59,0:24:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we can fully interact with
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.08,0:24:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,our SceneKit scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.59,0:24:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And the focus engine
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.43,0:24:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically takes care of
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.62,0:24:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,everything else for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.10,0:24:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I added two UIKit
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.28,0:24:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,buttons, UI buttons to the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.12,0:24:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom of our SceneKit scene by
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.99,0:24:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,just placing them on top of our
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.62,0:24:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,SK view and the focus engine
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.33,0:24:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,will automatically handle moving
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.60,0:24:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,focus between our nodes and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.88,0:24:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,these buttons.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.56,0:24:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And it'll do the correct thing
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.91,0:24:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter whether I'm on the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.14,0:24:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,left or right side of the board
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.10,0:24:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,hitting the correct button based
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.59,0:24:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,on what's geometrically closer
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.04,0:24:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to our nodes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.28,0:24:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, that's just a quick demo
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.62,0:25:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of SceneKit support for focus
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.19,0:25:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,interaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.52,0:25:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.05,0:25:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There are just a few more things
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.18,0:25:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep in mind when
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.11,0:25:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,implementing focus interaction
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.36,0:25:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,support in your SceneKit apps
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.85,0:25:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and games.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.78,0:25:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,First, SceneKit obviously
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.04,0:25:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,operates in three-dimensional
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.63,0:25:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,space, but focus interaction
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.11,0:25:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,operates in two-dimensional
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.52,0:25:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,space.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.39,0:25:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So how does this work?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.22,0:25:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Well when a user tries to move
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.85,0:25:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,focus in a certain direction
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.77,0:25:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to look for the next
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.02,0:25:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,focusable SceneKit node based on
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.02,0:25:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,its area as it's drawn onto the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.22,0:25:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.81,0:25:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, now that we support
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.83,0:25:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,focus interaction in SceneKit
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.97,0:25:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that means we're now also able
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.34,0:25:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to support your focusable
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.95,0:25:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,SpriteKit scenes that are
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.58,0:25:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,embedded within SceneKit scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.02,0:25:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And in fact, we automatically
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.20,0:25:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,support moving focus between
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.74,0:25:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,UIKit, SpriteKit and SceneKit
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.21,0:25:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,objects with no extra work
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.12,0:25:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,required on your part.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.09,0:26:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can build your user
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.68,0:26:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,interface using whatever tools
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.21,0:26:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,make the most sense for
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.28,0:26:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,different areas of your
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.12,0:26:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,application and focus
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.49,0:26:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,interaction support will just
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.67,0:26:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,work automatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.75,0:26:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And then finally, all the focus
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.63,0:26:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,APIs that we define in UIKit
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.35,0:26:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,using the UIFocusItem and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.12,0:26:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,UIFocusEnvironment protocols
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.36,0:26:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,also work for SpriteKit and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.45,0:26:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,SceneKit.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.49,0:26:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, those custom sound and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.93,0:26:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,animation APIs like Jon was
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.40,0:26:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,explaining earlier, those work
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.14,0:26:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,for SceneKit as well and really
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.27,0:26:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,helped to create a more
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.21,0:26:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,immersive user experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.86,0:26:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,To learn more about working with
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.26,0:26:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,both SceneKit and SpriteKit we
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.86,0:26:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,encourage you to check out some
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.15,0:26:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of these related sessions that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.23,0:26:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we're putting on this week.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.03,0:26:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Now for our grand finale today
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.85,0:26:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to talk about something
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.01,0:26:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that definitely affects all of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.39,0:26:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,us and that's debugging.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.92,0:26:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm happy to say that in tvOS 11
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.71,0:26:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we're introducing some great new
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.69,0:26:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,focus debugging tools that we've
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.12,0:26:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,built right into UIKit.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.98,0:26:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And first up is live focus
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.94,0:26:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,update logging.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.78,0:27:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,By including the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.19,0:27:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,UIFocusLoggingEnabled option in
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.93,0:27:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,your Xcode schemes launch
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.93,0:27:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,arguments you can turn on live
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.29,0:27:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,focus update logging.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.41,0:27:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what's really helpful about
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.46,0:27:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,this is that for each
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.96,0:27:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,programmatic focus update that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.56,0:27:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,gets logged we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.24,0:27:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,include a step-by-step outline
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.98,0:27:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of the preferred focus
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.19,0:27:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,environment's search logic that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.11,0:27:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the focus engine used to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.55,0:27:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,determine the next focus item.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.43,0:27:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, this is incredibly
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.76,0:27:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,helpful for diagnosing issues
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.12,0:27:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,where focus is not
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.07,0:27:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,programmatically updating to the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.63,0:27:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,item that we would expect it to.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.84,0:27:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And because these are logs this
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.31,0:27:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,can help you diagnose issues
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.56,0:27:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,like focus not updating to the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.34,0:27:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,correct item on app launch and
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.60,0:27:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,during transitions.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.88,0:27:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,However, this tool does come
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.93,0:27:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with one warning which is that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.23,0:27:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,please only use this for
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.36,0:27:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,debugging.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.46,0:27:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a nontrivial
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.00,0:27:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,performance cost that comes with
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.31,0:27:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,adding logging to your
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.20,0:27:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,application so you never want
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.63,0:27:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,this enabled for shipping
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.61,0:27:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,applications.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.93,0:28:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's focus update logging.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.66,0:28:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The next tool that we're
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.79,0:28:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,unveiling today is
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.73,0:28:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,UIFocusDebugger which is a new
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.02,0:28:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,class that we're exposing in
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.69,0:28:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,tvOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.33,0:28:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,UIFocusDebugger is a tool for
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.96,0:28:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,diagnosing focus related issues
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.71,0:28:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,at runtime in your app and this
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.93,0:28:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is really cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.47,0:28:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's structured like a miniature
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.90,0:28:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,command line tool that's built
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.64,0:28:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,right into UIKit available for
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.35,0:28:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.62,0:28:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,To take advantage of it all you
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.20,0:28:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,need to do is call any of its
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.78,0:28:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,methods from LLDB while your app
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.60,0:28:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is paused.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.09,0:28:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look at some of its
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.05,0:28:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,capabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.70,0:28:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The simplest one is that you can
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.41,0:28:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,simply call status to quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.20,0:28:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,print out the currently focused
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.23,0:28:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,item at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.10,0:28:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is often step one in
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.64,0:28:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,diagnosing some focus related
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.02,0:28:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,issue, especially if you can't
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.99,0:28:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,see where the currently focused
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.20,0:28:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,item is.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.20,0:28:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, you can use the simulate
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.69,0:28:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,focus update request from
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.34,0:28:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,environment method to diagnose
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.31,0:28:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,issues related to your app's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.82,0:29:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,preferred focus logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.72,0:29:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Calling this method is similar
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.11,0:29:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to calling the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.10,0:29:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,setNeedsFocusUpdate API and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.92,0:29:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,having that focus update execute
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.55,0:29:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,on the environment that you pass
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.97,0:29:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.64,0:29:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But what's great about this is
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.24,0:29:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it outputs that same
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.60,0:29:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,step-by-step preferred focus
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.85,0:29:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,environment search logic that we
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.39,0:29:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,also include in the live focus
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.00,0:29:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,update logging.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.00,0:29:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But with this simulation method
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.24,0:29:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you can simulate any focus
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.82,0:29:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,update anywhere in your
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.74,0:29:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,application without having to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.89,0:29:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,actually trigger that focus
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.26,0:29:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,update manually in your UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.96,0:29:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, this helps with quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.52,0:29:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,diagnosing different preferred
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.25,0:29:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,focus environments issues in
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.89,0:29:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,different places of your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.18,0:29:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Personally, my favorite tool in
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.81,0:29:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,UIFocusDebugger is this next
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.13,0:29:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,method, check focus ability for
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.63,0:29:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,item.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.61,0:29:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is used to print out a
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.11,0:29:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,list of potential issues that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.25,0:29:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,may cause an item to not be
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.00,0:29:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,focusable.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.26,0:29:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We've all had that kind of issue
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.44,0:29:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,where there is some item on the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.89,0:30:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,screen that we expect to be
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.02,0:30:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,focusable, but for some reason
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.60,0:30:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we just can't focus on it and we
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.66,0:30:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,don't know why.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.56,0:30:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And in fact, there are many
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.08,0:30:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,different reasons why an item
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.92,0:30:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,might not be focusable and they
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.13,0:30:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,could be issues not just with
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.62,0:30:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that item itself, but with
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.31,0:30:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,ancestors of that item that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.68,0:30:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,affect their children.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.74,0:30:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, this is where this new
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.85,0:30:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,focusability for item method
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.83,0:30:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,really shines.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.23,0:30:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It will automatically detect and
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.27,0:30:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,diagnose all of these potential
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.86,0:30:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,issues for you and print out a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.66,0:30:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,list of the issues that it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.22,0:30:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,detects and this allows you to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.02,0:30:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,save a ton of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.09,0:30:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, investigating all of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.24,0:30:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,these issues on your own would
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.28,0:30:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,just be a huge waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.75,0:30:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And then finally, like any good
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.29,0:30:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,command line tool you can always
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.90,0:30:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,just ask UIFocusDebugger for
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.41,0:30:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,help and this is going to print
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.23,0:30:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,out a detailed list of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.58,0:30:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,instructions for each of the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.10,0:30:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,commands that are available and
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.09,0:30:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,so don't worry about remembering
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.22,0:30:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,all of these methods right now
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.66,0:30:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because the help command has you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.24,0:30:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,covered.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.31,0:31:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But the best way to show you all
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.54,0:31:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,these new tools is with a quick
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.67,0:31:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.09,0:31:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so I'm in the process
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.76,0:31:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of building a new tvOS
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.53,0:31:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,application, but I've already
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.16,0:31:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,run into some pretty serious
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.64,0:31:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,focus related issues so let's
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.06,0:31:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,see if we can figure out what's
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.43,0:31:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.19,0:31:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to build and run our
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.19,0:31:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,application.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.06,0:31:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so this is just a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.89,0:31:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,simple app that showcases some
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.44,0:31:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,my favorite movies and the first
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.16,0:31:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,thing you might notice is that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.99,0:31:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing appears focused
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.19,0:31:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,onscreen.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.77,0:31:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And in fact, if I swipe on the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.24,0:31:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,remote or if I try to move focus
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.83,0:31:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,around the screen using the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.78,0:31:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,arrow keys nothing appears
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.37,0:31:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,focused.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.49,0:31:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm at a loss here, don't
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.65,0:31:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,really know what's going, let's
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.09,0:31:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,see if UIFocusDebugger can help.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.93,0:31:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to go back to our
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.35,0:31:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,application, pause it, which
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.55,0:31:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,will be LLDB and like I was
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.96,0:31:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,saying earlier, a good thing to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.36,0:31:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,check is the status of the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.55,0:31:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,current focus system.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.47,0:32:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm going to type in
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.27,0:32:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,UIFocusDebugger status and these
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.76,0:32:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,calls work with both Objective-C
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.54,0:32:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and Swift as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.83,0:32:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And what status is telling me is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.83,0:32:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is an item currently
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.76,0:32:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,focused, it's one of those
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.90,0:32:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,poster cells.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.07,0:32:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But obviously, if we take a look
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.58,0:32:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't appear focused and so
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.36,0:32:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,this points to some kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.67,0:32:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,potential issue with the visual
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.23,0:32:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,appearance of our cells.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.83,0:32:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go to our storyboard to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.52,0:32:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,see if we can figure out what's
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.25,0:32:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.17,0:32:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, I've got my
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.71,0:32:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,storyboard, let's open up our
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.46,0:32:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,collection view and we have a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.78,0:32:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,template for our cell and the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.10,0:32:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,cell contains an image view.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.61,0:32:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And what we want is for that
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.77,0:32:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,image view when the cell is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.06,0:32:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,focused to float up above our
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.73,0:32:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.03,0:32:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And now I'm taking a look at
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.99,0:32:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,this I noticed that we forgot to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.54,0:32:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,switch on this adjust on
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.08,0:32:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,ancestor focus option and this
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.04,0:32:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is what creates that floating
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.16,0:32:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,effect and so that's probably
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.11,0:32:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,our issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.59,0:32:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's rerun our application and
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.56,0:32:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,see if that fixes it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.05,0:33:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Awesome, now we can move between
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.72,0:33:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,these cells, it clearly
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.68,0:33:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,indicates which cell is
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.85,0:33:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,currently focused with that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.85,0:33:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,floating effect so we're looking
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.51,0:33:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in better shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.90,0:33:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There is another issue with this
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.17,0:33:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,allocation though, which is that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.45,0:33:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't seem to focus on this
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.23,0:33:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,more info button that's in this
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.66,0:33:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom shelf of our app and I
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.48,0:33:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,don't really know what's going
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.24,0:33:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,on there, there's nothing I can
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.43,0:33:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,do from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.13,0:33:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's go back into our
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.11,0:33:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,application and see if we can
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.93,0:33:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,figure out what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.48,0:33:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to go to our
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.45,0:33:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,mainViewController, set up
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.24,0:33:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,breakpoints, let's trigger that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.01,0:33:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,breakpoints.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.10,0:33:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so this is a great
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.10,0:33:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,opportunity to use that new
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.21,0:33:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,check focus ability method.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.38,0:33:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to type in P-O
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.01,0:33:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,UIFocusDebugger.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.45,0:33:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What's great is that we get full
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.54,0:33:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,autocomplete support and we're
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.72,0:33:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,allowed to invoke this, we need
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.45,0:33:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,a Swift code.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.97,0:33:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's check the focusability of
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.24,0:33:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,our more info button which I
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.44,0:34:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,have an outlet referenced to.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.00,0:34:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so it detected an
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.51,0:34:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,issue and what this is telling
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.83,0:34:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,us is that the item is being
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.37,0:34:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,visually occluded, that's
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.21,0:34:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,visually blocked by some other
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.96,0:34:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,item on the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.51,0:34:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And it really helpfully even
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.92,0:34:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,printed out a reference to the
